# Mobile-First & Accessibility

## Mobile-First Mandate (Luke Wroblewski)

Design for the most constrained context first. If it works on mobile, it works everywhere.

**Constraints:** 375-428px width, touch only (imprecise, one/two thumbs), moving/distracted user, variable connection, seconds of attention.

## Touch Targets

- Apple HIG: 44x44pt minimum
- Material Design: 48x48dp minimum
- Comfortable: 56-64px for primary actions
- Spacing between targets: min 8px to prevent mis-taps

## Thumb Zone

Primary actions and navigation: bottom center (natural zone). Secondary: middle. Destructive/rare: top corners (stretch zone).

## Gesture Conventions (never override)

- Swipe right: go back
- Swipe left on item: contextual actions (delete, archive)
- Swipe down: dismiss modal/sheet
- Pull to refresh: refresh list
- Long press: selection/bulk mode or context menu
- Pinch: zoom
- First-time users don't know custom gestures — use coach marks or visual hints

## Offline & Poor Connection

- Show connection status when offline
- Cache critical content for offline viewing
- Queue offline actions, sync when connected
- Optimistic UI: assume success, revert on failure
- Never let the app go blank — show last known state

